==English==

====Etymology====
from [[Greek]] [[απόστολος]] (''apostolos''), "one sent forth".

===Pronunciation===
*[[received pronunciation|RP]]: {{IPA|/əˈpɒs(ə)l/}}

===Noun===
'''apostle''' (''plural:'' [[apostles]])

# One sent as an envoy or messenger
# In Christianity, used to refer to Jesus’s twelve disciples (and also those later addressed with this title, i.e., Paul and Barnabas).
#{{vulgar}} (''Cambridge'') Men who are plucked, refused their degree.
# A method of [[certify]]ing [[international]] documents. See [[apostil]]

====Derived terms====
*[[apostolic]]

